@sijie @merlimat I have one more suggestion on how to fix the split-package issue. How about extracting all the classes from the split-package into a separate module. I can do another fork and make the changes and test that they work with the java-module-system. Then I can provide a separate PR for it.

Any suggestions on a name for such a module?

I suggest calling the module pulsar-common-api and have it contain all classes from the org.apache.pulsar.common.api and org.apache.pulsar.common.schema packages now found both in modules pulsar-client-api and pulsar-common.

@hellozepp 

Sorry for late response. the code snippet you pasted is the feature I mentioned in #3941 

However the feature here is about doing the same thing when pulsar broker deleteInactiveTopic. In #3941 , users delete topic explicitly using pulsar-admin. In this issue, it is broker itself deleting the topics when they are inactive. Hope this give you the idea about what this issue for.

@Anonymitaet Good point. 
1. Concerning the heading capitalization, we have two styles: sentence-style capitalization and headline-style capitalization. Both are Ok. Currently, IBM, Google, Microsoft docs apply sentence-style capitalization, so we can also adopt this style, as long as we keep it consistent. 
2. Base verbs are much better than gerunds in heading. It's great that you point this out.

@merlimat 
Schema registry can avoid both s2 and s3 will be update successfully.
https://github.com/apache/pulsar/blob/master/pulsar-broker/src/main/java/org/apache/pulsar/broker/service/schema/BookkeeperSchemaStorage.java#L450

@grantwwu In Go it's already possible to configure. Take a look at the `Logger` in `ClientOptions`:
https://godoc.org/github.com/apache/pulsar/pulsar-client-go/pulsar#ClientOptions 

We should do something similar for Python as well and probably move the logger to Py `logging` by default.
